# `apps/web` stays in context — the production `build` stage runs
# `nx run-many -t build` which needs the full project graph (including the
# @nx/next plugin's view of apps/web). The `dev` stage's granular COPY
# omits `apps/web`, so apps/web edits don't bust the dev layer hash even
# though apps/web is in the context.
